                <details>
                  <summary class ="sum2">
                     Representing Relations Using Digraphs
                  </summary>
                  <p>
                    Relations can be expressed using Directed graphs (Digraphs),
                     in this elements of sets are represented by a point,
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    and all the ordered pairs are represented using an edge
                    with their direction shown using arrows.
                  </br>
                  </p>
                  <details>
                     <summary class="sum3">
                      DEFINITION 1:
                     </summary>
                     <p>
                       A directed graph, consists of a set vertices and a set
                       of ordered pairs of elements of vertices called edges.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                       The vertex from which the arc starts is called the
                       initial vertex , and the vertex where the arc terminates
                       is called the terminal vertex.
                     </p>
